<h1>bible-api.com</h1>

<p>This is a tiny little web app that provides a JSON API for grabbing bible verses and passages.</p>

<p>This service is provided by <a href="https://timmorgan.org">Tim Morgan</a>.
You can get the source code for this app and the open data for its database at
<a href="https://github.com/seven1m/bible_api">https://github.com/seven1m/bible_api</a>.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>

<pre><code><%= @host %>/BOOK+CHAPTER:VERSE</code></pre>

<p>You can get pretty crazy with book names and with verse ranges using commas and hyphens.
It mostly just works. (Though, if it doesn't, you can
<a href="https://github.com/seven1m/bible_api/issues/new">submit an issue</a> and let us know!)</p>

<h2>Examples</h2>

<dl>
  <dt>single verse</dt>
  <dd><a href="<%= @host %>/john 3:16"><%= @host %>/john 3:16</a></dd>

  <dt>abbreviated book name</dt>
  <dd><a href="<%= @host %>/jn 3:16"><%= @host %>/jn 3:16</a></dd>

  <dt>verse range</dt>
  <dd><a href="<%= @host %>/romans+12:1-2"><%= @host %>/romans+12:1-2</a></dd>

  <dt>multiple ranges</dt>
  <dd><a href="<%= @host %>/romans 12:1-2,5-7,9,13:1-9&10"><%= @host %>/romans 12:1-2,5-7,9,13:1-9&10</a></dd>

  <dt>different translation</dt>
  <dd><a href="<%= @host %>/john 3:16?translation=kjv"><%= @host %>/john 3:16?translation=kjv</a></dd>

  <dt>verse numbers</dt>
  <dd><a href="<%= @host %>/john 3:16?verse_numbers=true"><%= @host %>/john 3:16?verse_numbers=true</a></dd>

  <dt>jsonp</dt>
  <dd><a href="<%= @host %>/john+3:16?callback=func"><%= @host %>/john+3:16?callback=func</a></dd>

  <dt>random verse</dt>
  <dd><a href="<%= @host %>/?random=verse"><%= @host %>/?random=verse</a></dd>
</dl>

<h2>Translations</h2>

<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Language</th>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Identifier</th>
  </tr>
  <% @translations.each do |translation| %>
    <% next unless (book_name = @books[translation[:id]]) %>
    <tr>
      <td><%= translation[:language] %></td>
      <td><%= translation[:name] %></td>
      <td>
        <a href="/<%= book_name %>+3:16?translation=<%= translation[:identifier] %>"><%= translation[:identifier] %></a>
        <% if translation[:identifier] == 'web' %>(default)<% end %>
      </td>
    </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>

